   <text>
      <body>
         <head>To <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0025.xml"/>William Allwood</persName></head>
         <opener><placeName>Norwich</placeName><lb/><date when="1759-03-06">March 6, 1759</date><lb/><lb/>
            <salute>Dear Billy,</salute>
         </opener>
         <p>You spoil my plan. I had appointed, with God&apos;s leave, to be at
               <placeName>Wakefield</placeName> on <date when="1759-04-18">Wednesday, April
               18</date>. But you tell me I must be at <placeName>York</placeName>. If I must, who
            can help it? Then I must set out from <placeName>Epworth</placeName> that morning, dine
            at <placeName>Selby</placeName> about noon, and so go on in the afternoon for
               <placeName>York</placeName>.<note place="foot" n="1"><persName><ref
                     target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>&apos;s <hi rend="italic"
                  >Journal</hi> for <date when="1759-04-18">Apr. 18, 1759</date> (21:187 in this
               edn.) indicates that he did just this.</note> But I hope you will begin the building
            directly. I suppose Dr. <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0433.xml"
               />Cockburn</persName> has my plan.<note place="foot" n="2">Dr. <persName><ref
                     target="/persons/pers0433.xml"/>Thomas Cockburn</persName> of
                  <placeName>York</placeName>, a younger classmate of <persName><ref
                     target="/persons/pers2176.xml"/>CW</persName> at Westminster, who had become a
               supporter of the Methodist movement in <placeName>York</placeName>. He later moved to
                  <placeName>Jamaica</placeName>, where he died in <date when="1768"
               >1768</date>.</note> Lose no time. I have some money in my hands for you.<note
               place="foot" n="3">Probably funds raised for a new preaching house at
                  <placeName>York</placeName>.</note>
            <index indexName="biblical">
               <term cRef="1Sam21:8">The King&apos;s business requireth haste</term>
            </index>.<note place="foot" n="4"><index indexName="biblical">
                  <term cRef="1Sam21:8">1 Sam. 21:8</term>
               </index>.</note> You may still direct your letters to <placeName>London</placeName>.
            I am,</p>
         <closer><signed>Your affectionate friend and brother,<lb/><persName>J.
               Wesley</persName></signed></closer>
      </body>
   </text>
</TEI>
